1
00:01:40,660 --> 00:01:42,000
=What If=

2
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,980
=What If=

3
00:01:44,980 --> 00:01:47,820
=Episode 18=
(A Farewell Without A Goodbye)

4
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:14,730
(Xue Yuming: Xia Guo, are you busy?
Reply to me when you're free.)

5
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:18,659
(Xue Yuming: Move to my house.)

6
00:02:18,660 --> 00:02:20,359
(I'm still renting it.)

7
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:21,959
(Xia Guo: Thank you. No need.)

8
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:23,959
(Xue Yuming: Have you eaten?)

9
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:26,999
(Xue Yuming: Are you up?
Xia Guo: Yeah.)

10
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:29,039
(Xue Yuming: Are you asleep? Goodnight.)

11
00:02:29,040 --> 00:02:30,879
(Xue Yuming: Guo, take some time off.)

12
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:32,679
(You haven't used your annual leave
over the years.)

13
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:34,000
(Are you okay?)

14
00:02:39,900 --> 00:02:41,779
Alright.

15
00:02:41,780 --> 00:02:43,660
This is the modified proposal.

16
00:02:43,900 --> 00:02:45,760
See if you have any comments.

17
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:48,450
- I look forward to working with you.
- Thank you.

18
00:02:49,220 --> 00:02:50,260
That's great.

19
00:03:07,940 --> 00:03:10,409
Implement these as soon as possible.

20
00:03:10,410 --> 00:03:12,340
Especially the end of the year.

21
00:03:16,900 --> 00:03:19,820
Ms. Xia, do you want to check that out?

22
00:03:19,940 --> 00:03:21,130
I'm fine.

23
00:03:22,650 --> 00:03:24,499
Everyone must focus.

24
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:26,019
Don't ever lose focus.

25
00:03:26,020 --> 00:03:28,010
Get motivated. Got it?

26
00:03:28,180 --> 00:03:29,820
Got it.

27
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:44,890
Ms. Xia!

28
00:03:48,490 --> 00:03:50,129
The doctor recommends
that you get hospitalized.

29
00:03:50,130 --> 00:03:51,619
Take the doctor's advice.

30
00:03:51,620 --> 00:03:54,459
Your stomach problem, bronchitis,
and high blood pressure

31
00:03:54,460 --> 00:03:56,130
are too serious.

32
00:03:56,690 --> 00:03:59,540
No. I have a lot of work on my hands.

33
00:04:00,020 --> 00:04:01,450
Alright.

34
00:04:47,100 --> 00:04:48,300
Come in.

35
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:49,940
Mr. Wu.

36
00:04:50,250 --> 00:04:52,180
Ms. Xia, can I help you?

37
00:04:52,770 --> 00:04:55,890
I just finished a meeting this morning.
I want to report some things to you.

38
00:04:58,940 --> 00:05:00,500
What happened to your voice?

39
00:05:00,620 --> 00:05:02,530
I just have a cold and a little cough.
I'm fine.

40
00:05:03,570 --> 00:05:04,179
Well...

41
00:05:04,180 --> 00:05:05,450
Ms. Xia.

42
00:05:06,180 --> 00:05:08,530
You don't have to work so hard.

43
00:05:08,810 --> 00:05:09,859
We know

44
00:05:09,860 --> 00:05:11,130
all about your mom.

45
00:05:11,770 --> 00:05:12,619
You can use this time

46
00:05:12,620 --> 00:05:14,009
to take a long holiday.

47
00:05:14,010 --> 00:05:16,450
Get some rest and refresh yourself.

48
00:05:17,540 --> 00:05:18,820
I'm fine, Mr. Wu.

49
00:05:19,180 --> 00:05:20,420
Thank you for your concern.

50
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:22,889
But the marketing department
hasn't met your expectations.

51
00:05:22,890 --> 00:05:24,570
How can I rest?

52
00:05:27,300 --> 00:05:30,420
You're too stubborn.

53
00:05:31,060 --> 00:05:33,300
You're not the only one
in the marketing department.

54
00:05:34,570 --> 00:05:35,369
Sorry.

55
00:05:35,370 --> 00:05:37,299
I know

56
00:05:37,300 --> 00:05:40,690
you're trying to become official.

57
00:05:40,890 --> 00:05:43,210
This puts a lot of pressure on yourself.

58
00:05:43,770 --> 00:05:46,940
Of course, this is coupled with
my high expectations for you

59
00:05:47,250 --> 00:05:50,260
and the marketing department.

60
00:05:50,660 --> 00:05:53,180
It's beyond your abilities.

61
00:05:54,130 --> 00:05:55,809
I understand.

62
00:05:55,810 --> 00:05:57,369
You've worked very hard.

63
00:05:57,370 --> 00:05:58,860
I can see that.

64
00:05:59,060 --> 00:06:02,420
So take some time to relax.

65
00:06:02,690 --> 00:06:05,060
Release your tension.

66
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:07,890
Pay attention to work-life balance.

67
00:06:13,980 --> 00:06:16,180
Okay, I got it, Mr. Wu.

68
00:06:17,010 --> 00:06:20,300
I'll think about your suggestion.

69
00:06:21,620 --> 00:06:22,980
I'll tell you about work

70
00:06:23,180 --> 00:06:24,500
another time.

71
00:06:24,660 --> 00:06:25,820
Take your time. Take your time.

72
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:27,620
Take good care of yourself.

73
00:06:27,890 --> 00:06:29,210
Okay.

74
00:06:36,060 --> 00:06:37,560
(Chen Nan: We haven't talked
for a long time.)

75
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:39,010
(Do you have time to meet tonight?)

76
00:06:39,540 --> 00:06:41,380
(No. 18, Bund, Huangpu District.)

77
00:06:52,100 --> 00:06:53,330
What's wrong?

78
00:06:54,450 --> 00:06:55,820
You're so pale.

79
00:06:56,180 --> 00:06:57,530
Are you sick?

80
00:06:57,940 --> 00:06:59,329
I'm fine. I just have a little cold.

81
00:06:59,330 --> 00:07:00,860
I'll be fine after resting for a few days.

82
00:07:01,740 --> 00:07:04,210
Alright. Stop pretending.

83
00:07:05,180 --> 00:07:07,500
Didn't Wu just satirize you?

84
00:07:08,250 --> 00:07:09,530
You found out?

85
00:07:11,100 --> 00:07:13,209
I don't think I can stay
in Haowei any longer.

86
00:07:13,210 --> 00:07:15,130
Don't stay if you can't stay.

87
00:07:16,450 --> 00:07:19,180
I came here today to poach you.

88
00:07:19,770 --> 00:07:21,569
I joined a jewelry company

89
00:07:21,570 --> 00:07:23,500
and want you to come with me.

90
00:07:23,860 --> 00:07:24,860
This...

91
00:07:25,690 --> 00:07:27,330
This is so sudden.

92
00:07:27,370 --> 00:07:28,500
Can I do it?

93
00:07:28,540 --> 00:07:29,689
There's no doubt

94
00:07:29,690 --> 00:07:31,770
that you can't do it
in your current state.

95
00:07:34,210 --> 00:07:35,690
Xia Guo, do you know

96
00:07:36,180 --> 00:07:38,260
what I like most about you?

97
00:07:38,620 --> 00:07:41,449
It's your relentlessness.

98
00:07:41,450 --> 00:07:43,499
Whoever it is,

99
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:45,130
you don't care.

100
00:07:47,770 --> 00:07:49,180
Now great.

101
00:07:49,570 --> 00:07:50,539
When I saw you today,

102
00:07:50,540 --> 00:07:52,650
you became a total coward,

103
00:07:53,010 --> 00:07:54,619
You let reality beat you.

104
00:07:54,620 --> 00:07:56,249
You were defeated by Wu.

105
00:07:56,250 --> 00:07:59,000
You lost your aggressiveness.

106
00:07:59,210 --> 00:08:00,570
Maybe?

107
00:08:03,770 --> 00:08:05,130
I'm just a little scared.

108
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:06,940
You were right.

109
00:08:07,060 --> 00:08:09,500
This job is more important
than fairness.

110
00:08:10,370 --> 00:08:12,420
The more you're scared of others
bullying you,

111
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:13,940
the more they will bully you.

112
00:08:14,370 --> 00:08:16,689
The more you fear losing,
the more you'll lose.

113
00:08:16,690 --> 00:08:19,059
But I think I've worked very hard.

114
00:08:19,060 --> 00:08:21,330
That means
you're not working hard enough.

115
00:08:24,100 --> 00:08:27,650
Actually, everyone wants results.

116
00:08:28,180 --> 00:08:30,419
Only you should know the process.

117
00:08:30,420 --> 00:08:32,580
Do you have to explain to others?

118
00:08:32,850 --> 00:08:34,689
Do you want people to pity you

119
00:08:34,690 --> 00:08:35,930
and comfort you?

120
00:08:36,540 --> 00:08:37,209
Fine.

121
00:08:37,210 --> 00:08:39,220
Come to me when you
can't make a living for yourself.

122
00:08:39,260 --> 00:08:41,380
I'll make sure you can make a living
wherever I can make a living.

123
00:08:41,450 --> 00:08:42,969
If you don't have a place to live,

124
00:08:42,970 --> 00:08:44,059
come to my house.

125
00:08:44,060 --> 00:08:45,530
The couch is yours.

126
00:08:45,780 --> 00:08:46,299
Will you come?

127
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:48,419
Ms. Nan, how can you
make something so sweet

128
00:08:48,420 --> 00:08:50,380
sound so bad?

129
00:08:50,660 --> 00:08:52,779
I just want to vent to someone.

130
00:08:52,780 --> 00:08:55,100
I can't tell others.

131
00:08:57,300 --> 00:09:00,260
Tell others? Who are you gonna tell?

132
00:09:01,020 --> 00:09:03,290
Do you want me to introduce you
to some elites?

133
00:09:05,180 --> 00:09:08,209
You're still single yourself,
and you want to introduce me?

134
00:09:08,210 --> 00:09:09,810
I'm happy to be single.

135
00:09:10,490 --> 00:09:13,050
I'm comfortable on my own, okay?

136
00:09:13,180 --> 00:09:14,290
Comfortable, comfortable.

137
00:09:14,490 --> 00:09:18,380
I'm not trapped by love like you.

138
00:09:18,850 --> 00:09:21,050
Are you still thinking about Xue Yuming?

139
00:09:22,810 --> 00:09:24,010
No.

140
00:09:26,260 --> 00:09:28,740
But honestly, I suggest you

141
00:09:28,810 --> 00:09:31,100
to forget about him.

142
00:09:31,180 --> 00:09:33,530
Really. Because I know him too well.

143
00:09:33,810 --> 00:09:35,379
He's your standard

144
00:09:35,380 --> 00:09:37,050
refined egoist.

145
00:09:37,540 --> 00:09:41,010
Do you think someone like him
is worth your energy and time?

146
00:09:41,210 --> 00:09:42,689
You'd better pull yourself together

147
00:09:42,690 --> 00:09:45,050
and fight with me, okay?

148
00:09:50,540 --> 00:09:51,810
Okay.

149
00:09:53,260 --> 00:09:54,650
I'll pull myself together.

150
00:09:55,450 --> 00:09:56,860
Hurry and eat. The food's getting cold.

151
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:19,339
Who are you looking for?

152
00:10:19,340 --> 00:10:20,499
I'm here for Allen.

153
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:21,259
Who?

154
00:10:21,260 --> 00:10:23,060
Get Allen for me.

155
00:10:23,930 --> 00:10:26,820
Allen, Allen, someone's here for you.

156
00:10:26,890 --> 00:10:28,010
Coming.

157
00:10:28,810 --> 00:10:29,649
Why are you here?

158
00:10:29,650 --> 00:10:31,259
I was about to find you.

159
00:10:31,260 --> 00:10:32,929
What are you doing? It's so noisy.

160
00:10:32,930 --> 00:10:34,820
I'm having a party on the weekend,
of course.

161
00:10:34,890 --> 00:10:36,409
You're not sleeping so early, are you?

162
00:10:36,410 --> 00:10:38,250
I can't sleep even if I want to.

163
00:10:38,570 --> 00:10:40,460
Since you can't sleep, come in.

164
00:10:45,570 --> 00:10:46,529
This is the dress code

165
00:10:46,530 --> 00:10:48,090
for our party today.

166
00:10:48,570 --> 00:10:49,580
Pajamas.

167
00:10:56,770 --> 00:10:58,970
Do people really hold such parties?

168
00:10:59,260 --> 00:11:00,619
Don't you guys sleep?

169
00:11:00,620 --> 00:11:03,569
We've been going to bed
before dawn for a month.

170
00:11:03,570 --> 00:11:05,339
So we need to celebrate it, of course.

171
00:11:05,340 --> 00:11:06,569
Is that worth celebrating?

172
00:11:06,570 --> 00:11:07,420
Of course.

173
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:14,569
Aren't you going to
break your streak today?

174
00:11:14,570 --> 00:11:16,700
Who cares? It's fun.

175
00:11:17,290 --> 00:11:19,169
Are these all your friends?

176
00:11:19,170 --> 00:11:21,580
Yeah, these are my best friends.

177
00:11:21,690 --> 00:11:23,420
How energetic.

178
00:11:23,860 --> 00:11:26,219
These are all people I met at the bar.

179
00:11:26,220 --> 00:11:27,139
Zhang Sen.

180
00:11:27,140 --> 00:11:29,569
His ancestors made Nv Er Hong
in Shaoxing.

181
00:11:29,570 --> 00:11:30,409
He's amazing.

182
00:11:30,410 --> 00:11:31,979
When he was 16,
he came to Shanghai alone

183
00:11:31,980 --> 00:11:33,409
to learn mixology.

184
00:11:33,410 --> 00:11:34,370
Pretty lady.

185
00:11:34,410 --> 00:11:35,529
This is my neighbor.

186
00:11:35,530 --> 00:11:37,099
This is my neighbor, Xia Guo.

187
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:38,370
Who?

188
00:11:39,290 --> 00:11:41,259
It doesn't matter. Let's dance!

189
00:11:41,260 --> 00:11:42,820
Okay.

190
00:11:57,930 --> 00:11:58,809
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

191
00:11:58,810 --> 00:12:00,099
Here's to Xia Guo!

192
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:02,300
Cheers!

193
00:12:27,930 --> 00:12:29,340
Did you get your heart broken?

194
00:12:31,570 --> 00:12:33,210
Look at you.

195
00:12:33,290 --> 00:12:35,540
I know what's going on
without you telling me.

196
00:12:35,980 --> 00:12:37,250
Long-distance relationships

197
00:12:37,410 --> 00:12:39,889
are sad, nerve-racking and don't work.

198
00:12:39,890 --> 00:12:43,660
No, we're just contacting lesser.

199
00:12:44,100 --> 00:12:45,139
So I think it's pointless.

200
00:12:45,140 --> 00:12:47,689
So become a career woman
and work on your career.

201
00:12:47,690 --> 00:12:49,700
It's not that easy to be a career woman.

202
00:12:49,890 --> 00:12:51,490
They're very lonely.

203
00:12:53,020 --> 00:12:55,529
It sounds like your love life and career

204
00:12:55,530 --> 00:12:56,940
aren't doing well.

205
00:12:57,140 --> 00:12:58,259
How do you know?

206
00:12:58,260 --> 00:12:59,420
I just want to say

207
00:12:59,890 --> 00:13:01,739
you don't have to be
so hard on yourself.

208
00:13:01,740 --> 00:13:02,850
You know that?

209
00:13:03,100 --> 00:13:04,289
Your bullies

210
00:13:04,290 --> 00:13:06,769
are enjoying themselves.

211
00:13:06,770 --> 00:13:08,139
Why are you so hard

212
00:13:08,140 --> 00:13:09,780
on yourself?

213
00:13:10,530 --> 00:13:12,460
You'll have to make a choice, right?

214
00:13:12,740 --> 00:13:13,979
You can't just

215
00:13:13,980 --> 00:13:15,580
go with the flow.

216
00:13:31,460 --> 00:13:32,619
Let me tell you a solution.

217
00:13:32,620 --> 00:13:34,700
You can use it later
when you have to make a choice.

218
00:13:34,930 --> 00:13:36,660
Do you want it? Here.

219
00:13:37,340 --> 00:13:38,339
What?

220
00:13:38,340 --> 00:13:39,370
Look.

221
00:13:39,570 --> 00:13:41,210
You see that guy down there?

222
00:13:42,050 --> 00:13:43,610
Once he finishes his call,

223
00:13:44,340 --> 00:13:46,529
you'll choose option A

224
00:13:46,530 --> 00:13:48,010
if he goes to the left.

225
00:13:48,020 --> 00:13:49,739
If he goes to the right, it's option B.

226
00:13:49,740 --> 00:13:50,970
What do you think?

227
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:53,809
Is that just going with the flow?

228
00:13:53,810 --> 00:13:55,979
Don't get discouraged. Try it.

229
00:13:55,980 --> 00:13:57,370
Figure out the option you want

230
00:13:57,570 --> 00:13:59,099
and close your eyes.

231
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:00,420
Close them.

232
00:14:04,290 --> 00:14:06,130
When you open your eyes

233
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:07,529
and find the option

234
00:14:07,530 --> 00:14:08,890
to be what you want,

235
00:14:09,020 --> 00:14:11,010
you'll be happy.

236
00:14:11,020 --> 00:14:12,289
But if the result

237
00:14:12,290 --> 00:14:13,890
is different from what you want,

238
00:14:14,100 --> 00:14:16,180
you may be disappointed
and even frustrated.

239
00:14:16,620 --> 00:14:19,099
But that frustration
will also remind you

240
00:14:19,100 --> 00:14:21,460
what you really want.

241
00:14:21,930 --> 00:14:24,490
And you'll also know what to do.

242
00:14:28,690 --> 00:14:30,780
(Each of us makes a choice)

243
00:14:30,810 --> 00:14:33,700
(about A or B every day.)

244
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:35,660
(Just like what Allen said,)

245
00:14:36,050 --> 00:14:37,460
(no matter what you choose,)

246
00:14:37,740 --> 00:14:39,370
(it's probably not too bad.)

247
00:14:39,810 --> 00:14:41,580
(But it's not that great either.)

248
00:14:41,770 --> 00:14:43,250
- (Everything's possible.)
- Three.

249
00:14:44,180 --> 00:14:47,409
- (Will life allow us)
- Two.

250
00:14:47,410 --> 00:14:50,010
- (to play games once in a while?)
- One.

251
00:15:11,120 --> 00:15:13,120
(Resignation Application)

252
00:15:17,020 --> 00:15:18,370
What's going on?

253
00:15:18,650 --> 00:15:20,340
Why are you resigning all of a sudden?

254
00:15:20,690 --> 00:15:21,890
Mr. Wu.

255
00:15:22,650 --> 00:15:23,809
I think the only way

256
00:15:23,810 --> 00:15:26,210
to give myself a good rest is to resign.

257
00:15:26,690 --> 00:15:28,580
I believe

258
00:15:28,740 --> 00:15:29,809
you can find

259
00:15:29,810 --> 00:15:31,940
someone more qualified
to be the director.

260
00:15:33,020 --> 00:15:36,210
Xia Guo, do you
have some misunderstanding?

261
00:15:36,220 --> 00:15:37,739
What I said to you earlier

262
00:15:37,740 --> 00:15:39,649
was out of concern for you.

263
00:15:39,650 --> 00:15:42,420
I don't intend for you to leave.

264
00:15:44,340 --> 00:15:45,169
I understand.

265
00:15:45,170 --> 00:15:47,180
But I think you have a point.

266
00:15:47,890 --> 00:15:49,339
I really need to make some adjustments

267
00:15:49,340 --> 00:15:51,460
in my life and work

268
00:15:51,980 --> 00:15:55,420
and think about my future.

269
00:15:56,930 --> 00:15:58,420
You're so determined.

270
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,940
It seems there's no way
I can change your mind.

271
00:16:01,050 --> 00:16:03,010
Thank you for helping me
make this decision.

272
00:16:05,460 --> 00:16:07,890
Okay, I respect your decision.

273
00:16:10,860 --> 00:16:12,060
All the best.

274
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:28,039
(Xue Yuming)

275
00:17:28,040 --> 00:17:33,880
(I don't want to go on like this.
Let's break up.)

276
00:17:35,460 --> 00:17:37,890
(When we figure out what to do next,)

277
00:17:38,370 --> 00:17:41,060
(we can say goodbye to the past.)

278
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:43,540
